Get funding rounds matching the specified filters.

This method builds a dynamic SQL query based on the provided filters. All filters are optional and can be combined.

Args: funding_round_uuid: Exact match for funding round UUID. investment_date: Exact match for investment date. investment_date_from: Filter funding rounds on or after this date. investment_date_to: Filter funding rounds on or before this date. org_uuid: Exact match for organization UUID (single). org_uuids: List of organization UUIDs to filter by (batch query). If both org_uuid and org_uuids are provided, org_uuids takes precedence. org_name_ilike: Search by organization name (case-insensitive partial match). This performs a JOIN to the organizations table to match by name. Can be combined with org_uuid or org_uuids filters. general_funding_stage: Exact match for general funding stage. stage: Exact match for specific funding stage. investors_contains: Check if investors array contains this UUID (as string). Note: This expects a UUID, not an investor name. Use investor_name_contains for name-based search. lead_investors_contains: Check if lead_investors array contains this UUID (as string). Note: This expects a UUID, not an investor name. Use lead_investor_name_contains for name-based search. investor_name_contains: Search investors by organization name (case-insensitive partial match). This performs a JOIN to the organizations table to match by name. lead_investor_name_contains: Search lead_investors by organization name (case-insensitive partial match). This performs a JOIN to the organizations table to match by name. fundraise_amount_usd: Exact match for fundraise amount. fundraise_amount_usd_min: Filter funding rounds with amount >= this value. fundraise_amount_usd_max: Filter funding rounds with amount <= this value. valuation_usd: Exact match for valuation. valuation_usd_min: Filter funding rounds with valuation >= this value. valuation_usd_max: Filter funding rounds with valuation <= this value. limit: Maximum number of results to return. offset: Number of results to skip (for pagination). include_organizations: If True, includes nested organization details for org_uuid, investors, and lead_investors. Returns FundingRoundWithOrganizations objects instead of FundingRound objects. order_by: Field to order results by. Must be one of: "investment_date", "fundraise_amount_usd", "valuation_usd". Defaults to "investment_date" if not specified. order_direction: Direction to order results. Must be "asc" or "desc". Defaults to "desc" if not specified.

Returns: List of FundingRound objects matching the filters. If include_organizations=True, returns FundingRoundWithOrganizations objects with nested organization data.

Raises: RuntimeError: If client is not initialized.

672                query += " JOIN organizations org ON fr.org_uuid = org.org_uuid"
673        else:
674            query = "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM fundingrounds"
675
676        if conditions:
677            query += " WHERE " + " AND ".join(conditions)
678
679        try:
680            count = await self._client.query_value(query, *params)
681            return int(count) if count is not None else 0
682        except Exception as e:
683            logger.error(f"Failed to count funding rounds: {e}")
684            raise

164            founding_date_from: Filter organizations founded on or after this date.
165            founding_date_to: Filter organizations founded on or before this date.
166            last_fundraise_date_from: Filter with last_fundraise_date >= this date.
167            last_fundraise_date_to: Filter with last_fundraise_date <= this date.
168            employee_count: Exact match for employee count range.
169            org_type: Exact match for organization type (investor or company).
170            stage: Exact match for funding stage.
171            valuation_usd_min: Filter with valuation_usd >= this value.
172            valuation_usd_max: Filter with valuation_usd <= this value.
173            investors_contains: Check if investors array contains this UUID.
174            general_funding_stage: Exact match for general funding stage.
175            num_acquisitions_min: Filter with num_acquisitions >= this value.
176            num_acquisitions_max: Filter with num_acquisitions <= this value.
177            revenue_range: Exact match for revenue range.
178            top_k: Number of results to return (default: 10).
179            index_name: Name of the Pinecone index to query. If not provided,
180                uses the default index from settings.
181
182        Returns:
183            List of PineconeOrganization objects matching the query and filters.
184
185        Raises:
186            RuntimeError: If clients are not initialized.
187            Exception: If query execution fails.
188
189        Example:
190            ```python
191            # Simple text query
192            orgs = await model.query(
193                text="AI companies",
194                top_k=10
195            )
196
197            # Query with metadata filters
198            orgs = await model.query(
199                text="healthcare startups",
200                org_status="operating",
201                total_funding_usd_min=1000000,
202                general_funding_stage="late_stage_venture",
203                top_k=5
204            )
205
206            # Query with date range
207            from datetime import datetime
208            orgs = await model.query(
209                text="fintech companies",
210                founding_date_from=datetime(2020, 1, 1),
211                founding_date_to=datetime(2023, 12, 31),
212                top_k=20
213            )
214            ```
215        """
216        if self._pinecone_client is None:
217            raise RuntimeError("PineconeClient not initialized. Call initialize() first.")
218        if self._openai_client is None:
219            raise RuntimeError("OpenAIClient not initialized. Call initialize() first.")
220
221        # Generate embedding for the text query
222        try:
223            embedding = await self._openai_client.create_embedding(
224                text=text, model="text-embedding-3-large"
225            )
226            logger.debug(f"Generated embedding for text query: {text[:50]}...")
227        except Exception as e:
228            logger.error(f"Failed to generate embedding: {e}")
229            raise
230
231        # Build metadata filter
232        metadata_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
233
234        if org_uuid is not None:
235            metadata_filter["org_uuid"] = {"$eq": str(org_uuid)}
236
237        if name is not None:
238            metadata_filter["name"] = {"$eq": name}
239
240        if categories_contains is not None:
241            metadata_filter["categories"] = {"$in": [categories_contains]}
242
243        if org_status is not None:
244            metadata_filter["org_status"] = {"$eq": org_status}
245
246        if total_funding_usd_min is not None or total_funding_usd_max is not None:
247            funding_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
248            if total_funding_usd_min is not None:
249                funding_filter["$gte"] = total_funding_usd_min
250            if total_funding_usd_max is not None:
251                funding_filter["$lte"] = total_funding_usd_max
252            metadata_filter["total_funding_usd"] = funding_filter
253
254        if founding_date_from is not None or founding_date_to is not None:
255            founding_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
256            if founding_date_from is not None:
257                founding_filter["$gte"] = founding_date_from.isoformat()
258            if founding_date_to is not None:
259                founding_filter["$lte"] = founding_date_to.isoformat()
260            metadata_filter["founding_date"] = founding_filter
261
262        if last_fundraise_date_from is not None or last_fundraise_date_to is not None:
263            fundraise_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
264            if last_fundraise_date_from is not None:
265                fundraise_filter["$gte"] = last_fundraise_date_from.isoformat()
266            if last_fundraise_date_to is not None:
267                fundraise_filter["$lte"] = last_fundraise_date_to.isoformat()
268            metadata_filter["last_fundraise_date"] = fundraise_filter
269
270        if employee_count is not None:
271            metadata_filter["employee_count"] = {"$eq": employee_count}
272
273        if org_type is not None:
274            metadata_filter["org_type"] = {"$eq": org_type}
275
276        if stage is not None:
277            metadata_filter["stage"] = {"$eq": stage}
278
279        if valuation_usd_min is not None or valuation_usd_max is not None:
280            valuation_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
281            if valuation_usd_min is not None:
282                valuation_filter["$gte"] = valuation_usd_min
283            if valuation_usd_max is not None:
284                valuation_filter["$lte"] = valuation_usd_max
285            metadata_filter["valuation_usd"] = valuation_filter
286
287        if investors_contains is not None:
288            metadata_filter["investors"] = {"$in": [str(investors_contains)]}
289
290        if general_funding_stage is not None:
291            metadata_filter["general_funding_stage"] = {"$eq": general_funding_stage}
292
293        if num_acquisitions_min is not None or num_acquisitions_max is not None:
294            acquisitions_filter: dict[str, Any] = {}
295            if num_acquisitions_min is not None:
296                acquisitions_filter["$gte"] = num_acquisitions_min
297            if num_acquisitions_max is not None:
298                acquisitions_filter["$lte"] = num_acquisitions_max
299            metadata_filter["num_acquisitions"] = acquisitions_filter
300
301        if revenue_range is not None:
302            metadata_filter["revenue_range"] = {"$eq": revenue_range}
303
304        # Query Pinecone
305        try:
306            filter_dict = metadata_filter if metadata_filter else None
307            response = await self._pinecone_client.query(
308                query_vector=embedding,
309                index_name=index_name,
310                top_k=top_k,
311                metadata_filter=filter_dict,
312                include_metadata=True,
313            )
314
315            # Convert results to PineconeOrganization objects
316            organizations: list[PineconeOrganization] = []
317            for match in response.matches:
318                metadata = match.metadata or {}
319                # Convert org_uuid from string to UUID if present
320                if "org_uuid" in metadata:
321                    try:
322                        metadata["org_uuid"] = UUID(metadata["org_uuid"])
323                    except (ValueError, TypeError):
324                        pass
325
326                # Convert investors from list of strings to list of UUIDs
327                if "investors" in metadata and isinstance(metadata["investors"], list):
328                    try:
329                        metadata["investors"] = [
330                            UUID(inv) if isinstance(inv, str) else inv
331                            for inv in metadata["investors"]
332                        ]
333                    except (ValueError, TypeError):
334                        pass
335
336                # Convert date strings to datetime objects
337                for date_field in ["founding_date", "last_fundraise_date"]:
338                    if date_field in metadata and isinstance(metadata[date_field], str):
339                        try:
340                            metadata[date_field] = datetime.fromisoformat(metadata[date_field])
341                        except (ValueError, TypeError):
342                            pass
343
344                # Add score from match
345                metadata["score"] = match.score
346
347                organizations.append(PineconeOrganization(**metadata))
348
349            logger.debug(f"Retrieved {len(organizations)} organization(s) from Pinecone")
350            return organizations
351        except Exception as e:
352            logger.error(f"Failed to query Pinecone: {e}")
353            raise

Query Pinecone for organizations matching text and metadata filters.

This method embeds the provided text using text-embedding-3-large, then queries Pinecone with the embedding and optional metadata filters.

Args: text: Text query to embed and search for (required). org_uuid: Exact match for organization UUID. name: Exact match for organization name. categories_contains: Check if categories array contains this value. org_status: Exact match for organization status (operating, closed, was_acquired, or ipo). total_funding_usd_min: Filter with total_funding_usd >= this value. total_funding_usd_max: Filter with total_funding_usd <= this value. founding_date_from: Filter organizations founded on or after this date. founding_date_to: Filter organizations founded on or before this date. last_fundraise_date_from: Filter with last_fundraise_date >= this date. last_fundraise_date_to: Filter with last_fundraise_date <= this date. employee_count: Exact match for employee count range. org_type: Exact match for organization type (investor or company). stage: Exact match for funding stage. valuation_usd_min: Filter with valuation_usd >= this value. valuation_usd_max: Filter with valuation_usd <= this value. investors_contains: Check if investors array contains this UUID. general_funding_stage: Exact match for general funding stage. num_acquisitions_min: Filter with num_acquisitions >= this value. num_acquisitions_max: Filter with num_acquisitions <= this value. revenue_range: Exact match for revenue range. top_k: Number of results to return (default: 10). index_name: Name of the Pinecone index to query. If not provided, uses the default index from settings.

Returns: List of PineconeOrganization objects matching the query and filters.

Raises: RuntimeError: If clients are not initialized. Exception: If query execution fails.
